Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo A pedestrian, Adewale Kazeem, lost his life in a road crash that occurred on Saturday at the Ayetoro junction, Osogbo, Osun State, when he was knocked down by a bus. The deceased was said to have died on the spot as a result of the injuries he sustained. His corpse, it was learnt, was deposited in the Ladoke Akintola University of Technology Teaching, Hospital, Osogbo, for autopsy. The Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Folasade Odoro, who confirmed the accident to our correspondent on Sunday, said a life was lost to the crash. She said, “A fatal motor/pedestrian accident occurred around 8.45pm on Saturday at the Ayetoro junction, Osogbo. “The accident involved a Toyota Coaster bus and a pedestrian, Adewale Kazeem, who was confirmed dead on the spot by a medical doctor. “The police deposited the corpse in the morgue of LAUTECH for autopsy. Investigation into the accident is ongoing.” Copyright PUNCH.
